bug.author: BreakingBI
bug.summary: Depracated Tensorflow Models should be labeled as such
bug.description:
[Enter feedback here] In the Azure ML Python SDK Reference Guide, we list all of the supported AutoML models. The Classification and Regression pages mention Tensorflow models. These models appear to be implicitly black-listed, even though they do not appear in the list of Blacklisted models in Azure ML Studio. If these are depracated, please update these documentation pages to reflect this. <denchmark-link:https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/python/api/azureml-train-automl-client/azureml.train.automl.constants.supportedmodels.classification?view=azure-ml-py>https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/python/api/azureml-train-automl-client/azureml.train.automl.constants.supportedmodels.classification?view=azure-ml-py</denchmark-link>

In the upcoming releases those TF models will be removed, too. Hence, those reference pages above should be updated plus this additional page where we're still listing the TF models (DNN based): <denchmark-link:https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/machine-learning/how-to-configure-auto-train#select-your-experiment-type>https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/machine-learning/how-to-configure-auto-train#select-your-experiment-type</denchmark-link>
